    "lateralMoveGuidance": [
      "Lateral moves keep the same level when complexity and impact expectations are equivalent.",
      "A temporary role expansion does not automatically justify a level change.",
      "Managers should use the same level language across product and tech to preserve parity."
    ]
  },
  "marketCalibrationNotes": {
    "notes": [
      "Product Manager and Software Engineer mid-level ranges are anchored using recent European benchmark data for mid-size companies in Germany, France, and the Netherlands.",
      "Senior Product Manager and Senior Software Engineer ranges are intentionally broader because a 500-person company may compete for talent across multiple EU hubs.",
      "Director and Head-of ranges reflect mid-size EU tech-company expectations and should be validated against local executive benchmarks before use for offers."
    ],
